    "summary": "Garrie van Pinxteren is a sinologist, journalist, researcher and university lecturer whose professional involvement with China spans a period of over thirty years. She has lived in China for more than ten years.\nShe first came to Beijing in 1982 as a student of ancient Chinese history in Shanghai. After obtaining an MA in sinology from Leiden University in 1988, she was an interpreter and an advisor on cultural exchanges with China. She moved to China in 1998 to become the first director of the Dutch Business Support Office in Hangzhou. In 2001 she moved to Beijing, where she was the China-correspondent for the newspaper NRC Handelsblad, for the national Dutch broadcasting corporation NOS and for Radio Netherlands Worldwide. In 2007, she published a book about the growing Chinese tendency to set its own international standards.\nSince returning to the Netherlands in 2009, she is senior research fellow at the Netherlands Intstitute  of International Relations Clingendael, lecturer on journalism at Groningen University and lecturer on the media and China at Leiden University. She acts as panel chair for China-related seminars and debates, writes columns and essays on China and regularly appears as China-specialist in the media. She is presently preparing a Ph.D. on journalists in China.",
