                    "description": "Garrie van Pinxteren is an East Asia correspondent for NRC media and for NOS News.  She is currently based in Beijing. As sinologist, journalist, researcher and university lecturer, her professional involvement with China spans a period of almost fourty years. \nShe first came to Beijing in 1982 as a student of ancient Chinese history in Shanghai. After obtaining an MA in sinology from Leiden University in 1988, she was an interpreter and an advisor on cultural exchanges with China. She moved to China in 1998 to become the first director of the Dutch Business Support Office in Hangzhou. In 2001 she moved to Beijing, where she was the China-correspondent for the newspaper NRC Handelsblad, for the national Dutch broadcasting corporation NOS and for Radio Netherlands Worldwide. In 2007, she published a book about the growing Chinese tendency to set its own international standards and in 2017 she published a book together with Frank Pieke on how Chinese people see the Netherlands.\nSince returning to the Netherlands in 2009, she was senior research fellow at the Netherlands Intstitute  of International Relations Clingendael, lecturer on journalism at Groningen University and lecturer on the media and China at Leiden University.",
